<dl id="n12213k"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12213k">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12213k"> 213(k)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Compostella deaf carman</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">On vient de nous apprendre que nos chansons de gestes devaient leur origine aux p&eacute;lerinages; Roland et l&apos;archev&ecirc;que Turpin Ont &eacute;t&eacute; chant&eacute;s sur la route de Compostelle; les p&eacute;lerinages m&egrave;nent &agrave; des f&ecirc;tes ou prolongent un &eacute;tat de f&ecirc;te sur toute l&apos;ann&eacute;e. <br><font color="green">[We have learned that the medieval epics have their origin in pilgrimages: Roland and Bishop Turpin were sung about on the road to Compostella; the pilgrimages led to festivals or prolonged the state of festival for a whole year]</font> <small> Stefan Czarnowski, <a name="SCSP" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#SCSP"><cite title="source">Le culte des h&eacute;ros et ses conditions sociale: saint Patrick, h&eacute;ros nationale de l'Irlande</cite></a> (1919) L</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
